## Summary

Inception complete for `kanban-view`. Artifacts in `specs/kanban-view/`:

- **questions.json** — 6 clarifying questions (drag-drop, view persistence, empty columns, feature visibility, count badges, priority filter). Autonomous mode → no human → resolved as documented assumptions per error-recovery extension.
- **spec.md** — Brownfield workspace summary, 5 user stories (P1 toggle, P1 board, P2 count badges/empty cols, P2 horizontal scroll, P3 priority filter), edge cases (cancelled/done/unknown-phase/empty/error/loading), 19 FRs, ViewPreference client-only entity, 7 measurable SCs, 13 assumptions, 10-row constraint register (internal conventions — no RFCs govern this feature), out-of-scope.
- **acceptance.md** — 33 Given/When/Then ACs with test level + verification each, constraint→AC map, test-level coverage matrix. Every edge state covered (empty/error/loading/unknown/cancelled/dark-mode).
- **repos.yaml** — single repo `devteam`, primary, frontend-only (no backend changes for read-only MVP).
- **audit.md** — inception trail with timestamps.

Key conservative decisions (all flagged `[ASSUMPTION:]`):
- **Read-only board for MVP** — no drag-and-drop phase changes (would need backend phase-transition API). Click card → detail page, same as list view.
- **No new API endpoints** — reuses existing `GET /api/features` + existing react-query cache (`queryKey: ['features']`). Toggling views does not refetch.
- **View persistence** — URL `?view=` (precedence, shareable) → `localStorage` fallback → default 'list'.
- **Cancelled features hidden; done features shown in Delivery; unknown-phase features in a trailing "Unknown" column** (defensive, prevents silent data loss).
- **Priority filter is Kanban-only for MVP** — list view keeps its existing sort controls.

Skipped: drag-and-drop, backend phase-transition API, pagination/virtualization, mobile stacked layout, status/date filtering, bulk actions, card reordering, animated transitions. Add when: feature volume grows beyond ~500, or users request active phase management via the board.

No code changed — specs only. Pipeline auto-commits `specs/` to the spec worktree on gate pass; no manual commit needed.
